
Release notes for gst-ipcam-server 0.1

This is a release announcement for gst-ipcam-server software package

gst-ipcam-server is a media streaming server based on gstreamer library, rtsp protocol and gst-rtsp-server project. The server implementation is for SH7724 streaming server prototype. The server support 3 codecs for images and video compression/format: H.264, MPEG4 and JPEG.

Current stable version is 0.1 and includes 2 components:
	* server: based on gst-rtsp-server project
	* client: a simple client used for demontration

Features of this release:
Server:
	* use library from gst-rtsp-server project
	* support jpeg, h264 and mpeg4 video stream separately but all can not run at the same time
	* RTSP request to connect to relevant server are: 
		- rtsp://ip:8554/mp4 for MPEG4 stream
		- rtsp://ip:8554/h264 for H.264 stream
		- rtsp://ip:8554/jpg for JPEG stream
	* both run at 25/1 fps
	* they can be opened with a movie player like mplayer or totem movie player
Client:
	* A simple demo client with gtk ui
	* support basic features:
		- connect/disconnect
		- play/pause stream
	* support both jpeg, h264 and mpeg4 video stream
	
Git repository:
	git://github.com/trungnt/gst-ipcam-server.git

